Delicta majorum immeritus lues

INS of the fathers thou must expiate -— Tin, Roman, thou restore the crumbling sanes And images begrimed with smoke and stains, And all the sacred places of the State.

The Gods all things originate and end ; To reverence of them thou owest thy sway 3 Thou rulest through the Gods thou dost obey 5 The Gods neglected countless evils send.
